A BOY SITS DOWN TO DINNER WITH HIS PARENTS IN THE BUILDING THEY TEND TO AND EXCLAIMS HE'S GLAD THEY ARE RICH!
THE FATHER EXPLAINS THAT THEY ARE IN FACT NOT RICH BUT POOR.
SINCE THEY LIVE IN A BUILDING THAT HOUSES A LIBRARY THE BOY BEGINS TO DIG IN DEEP TO THE WORLD OF ADVENTURES IN READING.
THE BOY GROWS UP AND EVENTUALLY GRADUATES COLLEGE.
HE GETS A JOB THAT INVOLVES BEING A COLLEGE PROFESSOR.
HE SHOWS HIS FATHER THE DOOR WITH HIS NAME ON IT AND HIS FATHER NODS IN APPROVAL OF HIS SON.
THE BOY IS EATING DINNER WITH HIS PARENTS.
HE TELLS THEM THEY ARE RICH.
THE FATHER SAYS THEY ARE POOR.
HE GRADUATES COLLEGE AND BECOMES A PROFESSOR
HE SHOWS HIS DAD HIS NAME PRINTED ON THE DOOR AT THE COLLEGE.
